---

## 🎯 Objective

Train a simple CNN from scratch on the CIFAR-10 dataset to correctly classify 32×32 color images into one of 10 classes:

| Label | Class |
|---|---|
| 0 | Airplane ✈️ |
| 1 | Automobile 🚗 |
| 2 | Bird 🐦 |
| 3 | Cat 🐱 |
| 4 | Deer 🦌 |
| 5 | Dog 🐶 |
| 6 | Frog 🐸 |
| 7 | Horse 🐴 |
| 8 | Ship 🚢 |
| 9 | Truck 🚛 |

---

## 🧠 Model Architecture

```
Input (32×32×3)
      │
Conv2D(32 filters, 3×3, ReLU)
      │
MaxPooling2D(2×2)
      │
Conv2D(64 filters, 3×3, ReLU)
      │
MaxPooling2D(2×2)
      │
Flatten
      │
Dense(64, ReLU)
      │
Dense(10, Softmax)  →  Output (10 classes)
```

| Layer | Output Shape | Parameters |
|---|---|---|
| Conv2D (32 filters) | (30, 30, 32) | 896 |
| MaxPooling2D | (15, 15, 32) | 0 |
| Conv2D (64 filters) | (13, 13, 64) | 18,496 |
| MaxPooling2D | (6, 6, 64) | 0 |
| Flatten | (2304,) | 0 |
| Dense (64) | (64,) | 147,520 |
| Dense (10) | (10,) | 650 |

---

## ⚙️ Training Configuration

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Optimizer | Adam |
| Loss Function | Sparse Categorical Crossentropy |
| Epochs | 10 |
| Batch Size | 32 (default) |
| Train Samples | 50,000 |
| Test Samples | 10,000 |
| Input Normalization | Pixel values scaled to [0, 1] |

---

## 📊 Results

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Training Speed | ~10ms/step |
| Test Accuracy | ~70–72% |
| Evaluation Steps | 313/313 |

> Sample predictions on 10 test images: **9 out of 10 correct** (frog misclassified as deer due to visual similarity in low-resolution images).

---

## 🚀 How to Run

### Option 1 — Google Colab (Recommended)

1. Open the notebook in [Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/)
2. Click **Runtime → Run All**
3. No setup needed — all dependencies are pre-installed in Colab

### Option 2 — Local Setup

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/29Rajeswari/Image-Classification-with-CNN.git
cd Image-Classification-with-CNN

# Install dependencies
pip install tensorflow matplotlib numpy

# Run the notebook
jupyter notebook image_classification_cnn.ipynb
```

---

## 📦 Dependencies

| Library | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `tensorflow` | Model building & training |
| `keras` | High-level neural network API (via TF) |
| `matplotlib` | Visualizing predictions |
| `numpy` | Array operations |

---

## 🔍 How It Works

1. **Load Data** — CIFAR-10 is loaded directly via `tf.keras.datasets`
2. **Normalize** — Pixel values divided by 255 to scale between 0 and 1
3. **Build CNN** — Two Conv2D + MaxPooling blocks extract spatial features, Dense layers classify
4. **Train** — Model trained for 10 epochs with Adam optimizer
5. **Evaluate** — Accuracy measured on 10,000 unseen test images
6. **Predict & Visualize** — First 10 test images displayed with predicted vs actual labels (green = correct, red = wrong)

---

## 💡 Possible Improvements

- Add **Dropout** layers to reduce overfitting
- Use **Batch Normalization** for faster convergence
- Increase epochs or add **learning rate scheduling**
- Apply **data augmentation** (flips, crops, rotations)
- Try deeper architectures like **VGG** or **ResNet** via transfer learning

